{
  "info": {
    "name": "HubSpot Recommendation Tool (Backend)",
    "_postman_id": "6c1c12c2-3a0a-4e73-9d44-51c93c19b9a1",
    "description": "Surface-level website technology detection + HubSpot-focused recommendations.\n\n## Purpose\nThis API analyzes a **single public URL** and returns:\n- Technologies detected (surface-level)\n- Categories and groups\n- HubSpot recommendations (config-driven)\n- Inbox-style Next Actions (config-driven)\n- Summary counts\n\n## Guardrails\nThis is **not** a recon/scanning tool:\n- No crawling\n- No enumeration\n- No brute forcing\n- No login bypass\n- No private network access (SSRF protections)\n\n## Environment variables used\n- `{{baseUrl}}` (example: http://localhost:3001)\n- `{{exampleUrl}}` (example: https://react.dev/)\n\n## Workflow\n1. Run **Health**\n2. Run **Analyze** (default)\n3. Try Analyze options (pretty / includeEvidence / includeSignals)\n4. Inspect loaded config via **Config** endpoints\n5. Inspect taxonomy via **TechDB**",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "description": "Use this folder to confirm the backend is running.\n\n### When to use\n- Before demos\n- After deployment\n- After changing `.env`\n- After updating the vendor dataset\n\n### Expected behavior\n- Should return HTTP 200\n- Response includes `{ ok: true }`",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health (default)",
          "description": "Health check endpoint.\n\n### Use case\n- Confirm API is reachable.\n\n### Expected response\n- HTTP 200\n- JSON:\n```json\n{ \"ok\": true }\n```",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('HTTP status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('Response is JSON', function () { pm.response.to.be.json; });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('ok is true', function () { pm.expect(body.ok).to.eql(true); });",
                  "pm.test('service field exists', function () { pm.expect(body).to.have.property('service'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Analyze",
      "description": "Core endpoint for running a **single-page, surface-level** tech analysis.\n\n## POST /analyze\nThis endpoint:\n1. Fetches a single URL (HTML + headers)\n2. Extracts public signals\n3. Detects technologies using fingerprint patterns\n4. Generates recommendations & next actions\n\n## Query parameters\n### pretty\n- `pretty=1` \u2192 pretty-printed JSON\n\n### includeEvidence\n- `includeEvidence=0` \u2192 removes evidence from detections (and any grouped detection views)\n\n### includeSignals\n- `includeSignals=1` \u2192 includes safe signal summaries\n  - meta keys preview\n  - script src preview\n  - cookie names\n\n> Raw HTML is **never** returned.\n\n## Notes\n- Only one URL is fetched.\n- SSRF protections block localhost/private IPs.\n- Response is cached by URL for a short TTL (configurable).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /analyze (compact)",
          "description": "Lightweight, frontend-friendly analyze endpoint (GET).",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/analyze?url={{exampleUrl}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "analyze"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "url",
                  "value": "{{exampleUrl}}"
                }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('HTTP status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('Response is JSON', function () { pm.response.to.be.json; });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('ok is true', function () { pm.expect(body.ok).to.eql(true); });",
                  "pm.test('technologies is an array', function () { pm.expect(body.technologies).to.be.an('array'); });",
                  "pm.test('hubspot object exists', function () { pm.expect(body).to.have.property('hubspot'); });",
                  "pm.test('hubspot.recommendations is an array', function () { pm.expect(body.hubspot.recommendations).to.be.an('array'); });",
                  "pm.test('hubspot.nextActions is an array', function () { pm.expect(body.hubspot.nextActions).to.be.an('array'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
